msgid ""
"The draw function samples 1/dt points from the schedule, therefore, for "
"an increased resolution in the plot you can reduce dt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/analog/analog.rst:167
msgid "Parameterized Schedules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/analog/analog.rst:168
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.analog.schedule.Schedule` coefficients can be symbolic, "
"enabling classical optimization loops or experiments that scan over a "
"family of time profiles. Coefficients can be instances of "
":class:`~qilisdk.core.variables.Parameter` or algebraic expressions "
"(:class:`~qilisdk.core.variables.Term`) built from parameters. The "
"schedule tracks every parameter it encounters so you can query or set "
"them later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../modules/analog/analog.rst:198
msgid ""
"For schedules, Hamiltonians, and interpolators, use ``get_parameters`` "
"and related accessor methods to inspect parameter state."
msgstr ""

